com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.repeatinggroup

Class RepeatingGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.repeatinggroup.RepeatingGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public final class RepeatingGroup
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents a FIX repeating group containing a collection of RepeatingGroupEntrys.

    A RepeatingGroup is defined by a MsgType, a NumInGroupTag, and a dictionary.

      • RepeatingGroup

        @Deprecated
public RepeatingGroup(int tag,
                                  String msgType,
                                  String dictionaryName,
                                  boolean ordering)
                           throws IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Creates a new repeating group without a parent store.

        A repeating group which has been created this way can be seen as a "template group" which can later be added to one or multiple messages or RepeatingGroupEntrys via the IRepeatingGroupAccessor.setRepeatingGroup(RepeatingGroup) method.

        Parameters:
        tag - NumInGroup FIX tag number
        msgType - FIX message type of message containing this group
        dictionaryName - FIX dictionary to look up the repeating group information
        ordering - ordering
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Message type is null, or dictionary name is null, or tag is not a valid NumInGroup tag

public RepeatingGroup(int tag,
                                  String msgType,
                                  String dictionaryName,
                                  boolean ordering,
                                  ITagValues parent)
                           throws IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Creates a new repeating group with a parent message.
        Parameters:
        tag - NumInGroup FIX tag number
        msgType - FIX message type of message containing this group
        dictionaryName - FIX dictionary to look up the repeating group information
        ordering - ordering
        parent - The parent ITagValues. Can be the message itself, or a RepeatingGroupEntry in case of nested repeating groups
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Message type is null, or dictionary name is null, or tag is not a valid NumInGroup tag

      • tagValues

        @Deprecated
public ListIterator<ITagValue> tagValues()
        Deprecated. 
        Iterates returning ITagValue objects. The numInGroup tag is the first ITagValue returned.

        Similar to tagValues() except that the iteration process should not create any new objects. This may be desirable for reasons of performance.

        The remove method is not supported by this iterator. Calling it will throw an UnsupportedOperationException.

        The ITagValue objects returned should be considered as read only. Changing the values of these objects is not guaranteed to change the underlying data.

        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValue's.
